# Reference Files — Index & Routing

> Source de verite pour savoir QUEL fichier lire QUAND.
> Mis a jour dans le meme commit que tout changement de reference.

---

## The 4-Layer System

| Layer | File | Purpose | Read when... |
|-------|------|---------|--------------|
| L1 — Architecture/Security | architecture-security.md | Rules, constraints, auth decisions, topology | Planning a new feature, choosing auth method, security review, DR questions |
| L2 — Coding Patterns | coding-patterns.md | Language skeletons, retry/error, test patterns, naming | Writing/reviewing code in project languages |
| L3 — Infra Endpoints | services-and-access.md | Servers, Docker, secrets, SPs, MCPs, API keys | Any infra work (SSH, Docker, secrets, MCP config, deploy) |
| L3 — Codebase Context | codebase-context.md | Module exports, schemas, key file inventory | Calling shared modules, modifying schemas, touching core interfaces |
| L4 — Task Instructions | .claude/skills/ + .carl/ | System prompts, quality gates, CARL rules | Delegating to agents, planning, execution |

---

## Routing Decision Tree

**Architecture or security question** → L1
**Writing or reviewing code** → L2 + L4
**Calling shared modules or modifying schemas** → L3 (codebase-context)
**SSH / Docker / secrets / MCP / deploy** → L3 (services-and-access)
**Delegating to agents or planning** → L4 (via CARL rules + skills)

---

## Staleness Detection Rule

If a name, endpoint, secret, or ID in any L1-L3 file doesn't match reality
(actual infra, actual codebase, actual config) → the file is stale.
**Fix it before proceeding with work that depends on it.**

---

## Maintenance Rule

When content in any L1-L3 file changes, update this index if the routing table is affected.
Reference file updates MUST be committed alongside the infra/code change they document.

